Here some ideas worth thinking about:  - Test are not for QA Team, good tests guide YOU and allow you to _rapidly_ and _radically_ refactor your code - If you're afraid to change something, you're dominated by your creation - Good architecture allows deferring decisions - Is your application build around a database?
